Security experts fear that as Isis loses ground in Syria, radicalised Europeans will return &amp; attempt to carry out attacks at home. LONDON - Britain's most elite troops are reported to be mingling with Christmas shoppers and New Year's Eve partygoers in the United Kingdom to counter the threat from Islamic State. Security experts fear that as Isis loses ground in Syria and Iraq, radicalised Europeans will return to their home countries and attempt to carry out attacks there. It s understood security officials are working undercover in major cities with ordinary shoppers and revelers.According to a British newspaper, snipers will also be ready to target suicide bombers moving through crowds.Meanwhile, it s understood British government has given permission to French plain-clothed teams to operate on ferries travelling to the UK from France, to help counter terror attacks.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)